            "description": "We are an interdisciplinary team training nano-electronic devices to solve simple classification problems and studying the scaling capabilities of such systems. Specifically, we use a genetic algorithm to train these devices on different binary classification problems and develop new methods for training that are scalable to large systems. In addition, I study the computational capacity of such systems and develop methods to scale them for solving complex tasks.\nI supervise Bachelor (2x) and Master (2x) students of the Twente University for their research leading to their thesis. ",
